  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Territorial Peace in Buenaventura- Childhood, Youth and Women- Testament, Church of Sweden</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Community inhabitants both in rural and urban settings, stay in their territories in a secure environment,  implementing peace propossals,  defending their territories and environment with women leadership. Humanitarian Spaces in Buenaventura are empowered and has strengthened their social fabric. Women gain power and autonomy within their communities to develop productive initiatives, and gaining a greater participation in the communities decisi&#xF3;n spaces. And playing a prominent role in the Humanitarian Spaces organigram. International actors keep on accompanying and supporting the Humanitarian Spaces.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Consolidation of the Territorial School for art, peace and envirnment belonging to the Peace University (UNIPAZ). First UNIPAZ unit buiding and working. Training to children, youth and women on: music, musical production, art workshops, organizing a youth commitee, sports and participation on community assemblies and decissions spaces within the Humanitarian Spaces in Buenaventura. Training on the creation of Cooperatives for women trying to put it in practice. Praying spaces for women. Workshops for women on leadership. Exchange meetings with some other women cooperatives in the country. Looking for International acompaniment to the Humanitarian Spaces. Witnessing, documenting and spreading posible human rights violations and attacks to Buenaventura inhabitants.</narrative>
  </description>
